The paper deals with a wireless storage system and focuses on improving the system reliability while enabling feasible decoding. This involves designing a new physical layer transmission protocol based on algebraic space-time codes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves wireless communication and distributed storage, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with system design and optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
